Figures for the Andalusia COVID vaccines paper

Á. Serrano-Ortiz & JL Romero-Cabrera; EPIDATA team

Variants distribution in Spain

Option A

Option B

Plots for vaccine effectiveness sub-analyses

SUB-A1: Vaccine effectiveness by number of vaccine doses (segregated by variant period and age group)

Groups manually excluded:

  • Cases before alpha rise, 60 years old or above, with more than one vaccine dose.
  • All cases before alpha rise, younger than 60 years.
  • Cases during alpha predominance, 60 years old or above, with three vaccine doses.
  • All cases during alpha predominance, younger than 60 years.
  • Cases during delta predominance, younger than 60 years, with three vaccine doses.

Groups automatically excluded:

  • Those with upper vaccine effectiveness estimation interval above 100%.
  • Those with lower vaccine effectiveness estimation interval below 0%.
  • Those with vaccine effectiveness point-estimate above 100% or below 0%.

SUB-A2: NO MANUAL FILTERS Vaccine effectiveness by number of vaccine doses (segregated by variant period and age group)

Groups automatically excluded:

  • Those with upper vaccine effectiveness estimation interval above 100%.
  • Those with lower vaccine effectiveness estimation interval below 0%.
  • Those with vaccine effectiveness point-estimate above 100% or below 0%.

SUB-B1: Vaccine effectiveness by time since last exposure: infection/vaccination (segregated by variant period and age group)

Groups manually excluded:

  • All cases before alpha rise, younger than 60 years.
  • All cases during alpha predominance, younger than 60 years.

Groups automatically excluded:

  • Those with upper vaccine effectiveness estimation interval above 100%.
  • Those with lower vaccine effectiveness estimation interval below 0%.
  • Those with vaccine effectiveness point-estimate above 100% or below 0%.

These analysis and plots are not suitable, since they are trying to portray vaccine effectiveness parametres that have been calculated on variables related to risk, not protection (as opposite to vaccine doses).

var_agegr_LASTIMMUN %>%
  filter(outcome == "hospitalisation") %>%
  filter(
    (original_model == "Before_60")
    | (original_model == "α_60")
    | (original_model == "Δ_Menor")
    | (original_model == "Δ_60")
    | original_model %in% c("Ό_60", "Ό_Menor")
  ) %>%
  filter(veffec_lower > 0 & veffec_lower <= 100) %>%
  filter(veffec_upper > 0 & veffec_upper <= 100) %>%
  filter(veffec > 0 & veffec < 100) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_errorbar(
    aes(x = predictor, ymin = veffec_lower, ymax = veffec_upper, colour = variant),
    linewidth = 1,
    width = 0.2
  ) +
  geom_point(aes(x = predictor, y = veffec, colour = variant), size = 3) +
  facet_wrap(~agegroup, nrow = 2, strip.position = "left") +
  scale_colour_manual(values = colours) +
  # scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 100)) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(vjust = 0.5)) +
  labs(
    y = "Vaccine effectiveness",
    x = "Time past since last exposure",
    colour = "Variant period",
    title = "Outcome: hospitalisation"
  )

SUB-B1 v2!: Risk of infection by time since last exposure: infection/vaccination (segregated by variant period and age group)

Groups manually excluded:

  • All cases before alpha rise, younger than 60 years.
  • All cases during alpha predominance, younger than 60 years.

Groups automatically excluded:

  • Those with OR point-estimate above 10.

SUB-B2 v2!: NO MANUAL FILTERS Risk of infection by time since last exposure: infection/vaccination (segregated by variant period and age groups)

Groups automatically excluded:

  • Those with OR point-estimate above 10.

Risk of infection by time since last exposure (segregated by number of vaccine doses and age groups)

Groups automatically excluded:

  • Those with OR point-estimate above 10.

ALTERNATIVE!! PREDICTOR: time past since last exposure (subset by nº of doses)

# df <- data.frame(edad = edades, rentabilidad = rentabilidad)
